<item>
            <title>[HBASE-6239] [replication] ReplicationSink uses the ts of the first KV for the other KVs in the same row</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6239</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ReplicationSink assumes that all the KVs for the same row inside a WALEdit will have the same timestamp, which is not necessarily the case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This only affects 0.90 and 0.92 since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5203&quot; title=&quot;Group atomic put/delete operation into a single WALEdit to handle region server failures.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5203&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5203&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixes it in 0.94&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12595151">HBASE-6239</key>
            <summary>[replication] ReplicationSink uses the ts of the first KV for the other KVs in the same row</summary>
