                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13396994" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 19 Jun 2012 19:16:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Easy fix in ReplicationSink, just set the ts that comes with each KV, then I&apos;m adding test that&apos;s also good for 0.94 and onward (and it passes).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13399417" author="tsuna" created="Fri, 22 Jun 2012 16:25:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would argue that this bug is not &quot;minor&quot;, because we&apos;re talking about data being corrupted by HBase.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13403319" author="stack" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2012 18:12:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pity this is so ugly:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+    HLog.Entry[] entries = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; HLog.Entry[3];
+    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; now = &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.currentTimeMillis();
+    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; i = 0; i &amp;lt; 3; i++) {
+      entries[i] = createEntry(TABLE_NAME1, 1, i, KeyValue.Type.Put, now+i);
+    }
+    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Kinda ugly, trying to merge all the entries into one
&lt;/span&gt;+    entries[0].getEdit().add(entries[1].getEdit().getKeyValues().get(0));
+    entries[0].getEdit().add(entries[2].getEdit().getKeyValues().get(0));
+    HLog.Entry[] entry = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; HLog.Entry[1];
+    entry[0] = entries[0];
+    SINK.replicateEntries(entry);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...but its not a blocker.  Commit.  Backport to 0.94?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13404047" author="jmhsieh" created="Fri, 29 Jun 2012 17:23:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Adding as a potential for 0.90.7 release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13412407" author="jmhsieh" created="Thu, 12 Jul 2012 00:25:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bumping to 0.90.8 &amp;#8211; I&apos;m personally not concerned about replication in 0.90.7&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13412564" author="tsuna" created="Thu, 12 Jul 2012 06:54:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This means HBase replication will still corrupt timestamps in 0.90.7, which in many cases makes replication useless.  Are you sure?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13412576" author="jmhsieh" created="Thu, 12 Jul 2012 07:18:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If this is not a blocker for 0.92&apos;s where replication is considered robust, I&apos;m not sure it should be a blocker on 0.90 where it is more experimental.  That said, if a patch lands for 0.90 I&apos;ll gladly accept it &amp;#8211; I&apos;m just not going to block a 0.90.7 because of it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13445666" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 05:04:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated to 0.92 branch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch, J-D.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review, Stack.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
